{
  "texts": [
    "Lastly, repetitive information (e.g., someone describes the same thing twice), and information unrelated to the event the participant is trying to describe (e.g., 'sorry for that cough!')",
    "are also considered external.",
    "The manual for the interview provides clear rules on how to divide up segments of text into individual details.",
    "For internal segments, each piece of information that tells us something more about the event is generally counted as a detail.",
    "For example, \"he had a hat\" is considered one detail."
  ]
}